<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-11302] Invalid time unit conversion causing write timeouts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11302</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve been debugging a write timeout that we saw after upgrading from the 2.0.x release line, with our particular workload. Details of that process can be found in this thread:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mail-archive.com/user@cassandra.apache.org/msg46064.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.mail-archive.com/user@cassandra.apache.org/msg46064.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After bisecting various patch release versions, and then commits, on the 2.1.x release line we&apos;ve identified version 2.1.5 and this commit as the point where the timeouts first start appearing:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/828496492c51d7437b690999205ecc941f41a0a9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/828496492c51d7437b690999205ecc941f41a0a9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After examining the commit we believe this line was a typo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/828496492c51d7437b690999205ecc941f41a0a9#diff-c7ef124561c4cde1c906f28ad3883a88L467&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/828496492c51d7437b690999205ecc941f41a0a9#diff-c7ef124561c4cde1c906f28ad3883a88L467&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as it doesn&apos;t properly convert the timeout value from milliseconds to nanoseconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After testing with the attached patch applied, we do not see timeouts on version 2.1.5 nor against 2.2.5 when we bring the patch forward. While we&apos;ve tested our workload against this and we are fairly confident in the patch, we are not experts with the code base so we would prefer additional review.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
